File: Thabiso Kutumela scored the only goal of the match in the 27th minute. PIETERMARITZBURG - Maritzburg United seem to be really unstoppable on Friday nights at Harry Gwala Stadium. The Team of Choice’s inspired run in the Absa Premiership continued on Friday night. Eric Tinkler’s men moved to the sixth spot on the log after defeating Amazulu in the KwaZulu-Natal derby in Pietermaritzburg. Thabiso Kutumela scored the only goal of the match in the 27th minute. Pressure is mounting on the relegation-threatened Usuthu side. The result sees Jozef Vukusic’s charges suffer their third defeat on the trot in the New Year after losing to Mamelodi Sundowns and Supersport United.